          <p class="hp "><em>6. Intense side stretch(Parsvottanasana) </em></p>
        <p class="hp "><em>How to do it</em></p>
        <p class="pb">  Start in Mountain Pose. Step your left foot back and place it flat on the floor at a 45-degree angle. Ground down into both feet and lift up through the thighs.  Place your hands on your hips. Rotate your torso forward. Hinge at the hips and lengthen your spine over the front leg. Lift away from the floor and broaden across the chest.
            Pro tip: If it’s accessible to you, join your palms to touch behind your upper back. For tight shoulders, grab opposite elbows behind your back.</p>
        <p class="hp "><em>The benefits</em></p>
        <p class="pb">  The pose helps calm the mind and stretches your spine, shoulders, wrists, hips, and hamstrings.</p>

      </div>

